t gcc to just randomly assign bits, and want things to be <br />convenient in that situation.<br /><br />But _if_ you care about the underlying format, then inevitably the <br />bitfield costs will be much higher than just using bit operations on a<br />"u32" or similar. Your helper macros are horrible compared to just making <br />the bits work out right to begin with, and using the standard byte order <br />things.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
